def generate_strings(char_set, length):
    strings = []
    n = len(char_set)

    def generate_strings_recur(sub, count):
        if count == 0:
            strings.append(sub)
            return
        for i in range(n):
            new_sub = sub + char_set[i]
            generate_strings_recur(new_sub, count - 1)
    count = length
    sub = 'MUTATED'
    generate_strings_recur(sub, count)
    return strings
